               <p>JOHN THOMAS COX. I <rs id="t18310106-141-viclabel807" type="occupation">keep a bookseller's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-141-victim1248 t18310106-141-viclabel807"></join>, in <placeName id="t18310106-141-crimeloc808">Red Lion-court, Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-141-crimeloc808" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-court, Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-141-crimeloc808" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-141-off805 t18310106-141-crimeloc808"></join>. On the 21st of December, about ten o'clock in the evening, I was looking through the parlour window, and saw the prisoner come into the shop, put his arm across the top counter, and take three Prayer-books; I instantly opened the door, ran out, and took him about ten yards off, with them - he said he was a distressed tradesman, and was sorry for what he had done.</p>
